-- Takefuji May File for Bankruptcy Protection as Refunds Mount, Nikkei Says
-- B y   F e r g u s   M a g u i r e
-- 2010-09-26T22:28:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/takefuji-may-file-for-bankruptcy-protection-as-refunds-mount-nikkei-says.html
Takefuji Corp., a Japanese consumer
lender, may file for bankruptcy protection amid rising refunds
to borrowers for interest overpayments, Nikkei English News
said, without citing anyone.   The company’s liabilities were 430 billion yen as of June
30, the report said.  President Akira Kiyokawa and Executive Vice President
Taketeru Takei are expected to step down, the report said.    Calls to the Tokyo headquarters of Takefuji before regular
business hours weren’t answered.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fergus Maguire at 
 fmaguire@bloomberg.net  